A. schema_evolution

    python src/schema_evolution.py -r dwh  // build and align dwh according .env 

    python src/schema_evolution.py -r <path-to-new-file>
        
        example:
        python src/schema_evolution.py -r datasets/fin/function_liquidity_kpi_max_daily_expected_cash_outflows_to_total_hqla

B. fill the tables:
    python src/main.py -t dwh -r core

    example: python src/main.py -t dwh -r loans/dwh_dim_loans_attributes_templates.sql    


Steps to update table columns:
1. python files are the build of the object, add the columns
2. Go to db_schema_utils -> enable_schema_evolution -> True  // false is default, change  True to define the schema_evulution job to move all tables, compare the changes and add the new fields
3. run A 
4. run B to fill the data


create new schema in raw and objects in the schema

python src/init_raw_cdc_tables.py -r raw/<new schema>